info.name: walletd
info.description:
The walletd API provides a comprehensive interface for managing wallets on the Sia network. Its client-server architecture gives you the flexibility to access your funds from anywhere, on any device, without compromising the security of your private keys. The server is agnostic, so you can derive those keys from a 12-word seed phrase, a legacy (`siad`) 28-word phrase, a Ledger hardware wallet, or another preferred method.

Developers can build integrations leveraging its powerful JSON API. Whether you're using a single address or millions, `walletd` scales to your needs.

request.description: Returns all transactions currently in the transaction pool. Includes transactions not associated with any registered wallet.

response.name: Get Transactions

request.description:
Returns the current fee to broadcast a transaction. The fee is the number of Hastings per byte. To calculate how much a transaction will cost to broadcast, take its encoded size and multiply it by the returned value.

Most transactions are less than 1000 bytes. Using 1000 bytes as a constant size will work for most transactions.

item.name: Construct

variable.description: The ID of the wallet to use for funding the transaction

request.description:
Constructs a transaction sending the siacoin and siafunds to the recipients. The UTXOs used to fund the transaction will be locked for further use. If you no longer want to broadcast the transaction, you should call `/release` to release the UTXOs to be used in other transactions.

After construction, the transaction must be signed using the correct private keys before it can be broadcast. Signing is not handled by \`walletd\` for increased security.

The value for the Siacoins is in Hastings (1 SC = 10^24 H)

request.description:
Reserves UTXOs preventing them from being used by the fund endpoint. To unlock the UTXOs and allow other transactions to use them, call the release endpoint.

Duration is the time to lock the UTXOs in nanoseconds. If duration is zero, the outputs will be locked for 10 minutes.
Release unlocks UTXOs so they can be used to fund transactions when calling the fund endpoint.

item.description:
The address endpoints are used to query data associated with a specific address. These endpoints are primarily targeted at wallet developers and exchanges using "full" index mode.

- When index mode is "personal," the address must be associated with an existing wallet.
    
- When index mode is "full," data can be retrieved for any address.

variable.description: The id of the event to retrieve

request.description:
Returns data on a confirmed event

- In "personal" mode, the events must be relevant to an existing wallet.
    
- In "full" mode, any event that occurred on chain can be used.
